  "comments": "<p>Under backlight the whole security strip can be seen. Repeated on it is “20 COM”</p><p><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/67576c1c63e91.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/67576c1c63e91.jpg\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>UV activity (365nm). On the obverse only the serial number fluoresces. The yellow part is reflection:</p><p><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/67576c390777c.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/67576c390777c.jpg\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>On the reverse only the green square with 20 COM in it fluoresces, the red and yellow parts are reflection:</p><p><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/67576c46a1795.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/67576c46a1795.jpg\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The reverse under UV, this time at 254nm:</p><p><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/67576fbd7324f.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/67576fbd7324f.jpg\"></a><br>© Brandon Bertolli</p>",
